## 1. Directory Structure
- /src/app: Next.js routing shells only (One-liners that return a Module).
- /src/modules: Page Assemblers (Combines a Layout with one or more Features).
- /src/layouts: Screen skeletons & physics (e.g., God Box, Sidebar, Auth Frame).
- /src/components/features: The "Brain" (Stateful UI logic, Supabase calls, specific domain views).
- /src/components/ui: Pure UI Atoms (Design system: Buttons, Badges, standard Cards).
- /src/api: Shared data-fetching logic and direct database interactions.
- /src/hooks: Logic-only custom React hooks.
- /src/lib: Shared utilities, Supabase client, and TypeScript types.

## 2. Refactoring Principles
- "Module First": No complex logic in /src/app. Always create a Module to assemble the page.
- "Stage Ownership": The DashboardStage component owns the 3-row vertical flex stack and the Stage-Right toolbar rail.
- "Logic Extraction": Keep business logic in Features/Hooks. Keep assembly logic in Modules. Keep physical structure in Layouts.
- "Color Consistency": Never use hardcoded HEX codes. Use Tailwind brand names (brand-purple, brand-pink, brand-cream) defined in tailwind.config.js. If you find or need to use colors other than the brand colors, please prompt me to add them as brand-colors in tailwind.config.js.
- "Stable Physics": Use Flexbox for all layout alignment. Avoid JS-based DOM measurements (like getBoundingClientRect) for UI positioning unless absolutely necessary.
- "Bridge & Burn": When moving files, update all imports first, verify the view works, then delete the old source files immediately to prevent "file ghosting."